The paper proposes a novel support detection-based channel training method for frequency selective millimeter-wave (mm-wave) multiple-input-multiple-output system with lens antenna arrays. This involves signal processing, communication networks, and control systems, which are all covered by the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). However, since the paper focuses more on signal processing and communication networks, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
